# gen160 E1: a social composition the current brain does NOT fully pass — the
# recorded growth edge for E1's social half. Two near-misses, both fixable with
# GENERIC parser work (not a bespoke handler), so the class is generic-parser:
#   1. bare self-introduction "i'm vera" should feed the SAME name memory that
#      "my name is X" / "call me X" already fill (a one-frame intake extension).
#   2. an unbound pronoun "she" should be allowed to bind to a named personal
#      entity (the cat), not only to KB-fact subjects — composing possession
#      memory with discourse reference.
# Until then these turns wall; the bench records that honestly.
#subsystems: self-introduction, possession-memory, discourse-reference, name-recall
#expect: gap
#class: generic-parser
> hi, i'm vera
< nice to meet you vera
> i have a cat named smoke
< your cat is called smoke
> is she a robot?
< no
> what is my name?
< your name is vera